      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAZI DAIS (6) is in terrific form having won all three starts this time. Came from this barrier in the latest outing and worked to the front before drawing away to record a dominant win at Bunbury, cruising home by 13m. Returns to the city but has won three of five attempts at this circuit and distance so can continue the winning run. CAPTAIN STIRLING (3) gave his opponents no chance first up when he drew wider and worked to find the front before he cruised to a 15 metre victory at Pinjarra. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position and is three from three when second-up so can strike again. ALTA TRIBUTE (8) draws wide but will be fitter for a respectable third when resuming at this circuit and distance and he goes very well second-up with two wins and a placing from three attempts. BELLY UP (5) has come from the back row for second in two starts since a spell. Could be ready to peak.",
